{"TopicId":213958,"ForumId":120,"TopicTitle":"Telescopes","CreatedByName":"Got Dustyn","CreatedById":227004,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-28T21:01:20Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Got Dustyn","CreatedById":227004,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-28T21:01:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe need more reasons to send rockets to space for progression in game. What if we add telescopes! If we add a science instrument to be able to detect other worlds and other solar systems and bodies. It would add to the game.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nImagine, the only thing in the solar system is Kerbin, Mun, and the Sun. We want to explore! We send a telescope to low orbit and we discover a new moon, a new planet to explore and then we would have that accomplishment in finding new celestial bodies that we can visit!\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Buzz313th","CreatedById":149043,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-28T21:47:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI like this idea.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"USAGuerrilla","CreatedById":111854,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-28T22:26:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nneat idea\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"USAGuerrilla","CreatedById":111854,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-28T23:36:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nalso maybe planets are hidden on high difficulty, and you can see them through telescope and calculate their orbits.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tazooka","CreatedById":226666,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-02T12:31:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d love this idea!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI often made \u0027telescopes\u0027 in KSP 1 just for fun. But it would make sense to have this as part of the Interstellar or Colonies update\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheArturro","CreatedById":225694,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-02T14:37:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt would work great for interstellar travel!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo travel to a different star system you first need to discover it with a space telescope.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tazooka","CreatedById":226666,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-02T14:55:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224249837\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022213958\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221677767857\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022225694\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022TheArturro\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 minutes ago, TheArturro said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt would work great for interstellar travel!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo travel to a different star system you first need to discover it with a space telescope.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, that\u0027d be amazing and fun\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003EAlso you have a type in your signature\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nQuote\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#f9f9f9;color:#576170;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E24 Frebruary 2023\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFebruary\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"zeekzeek22","CreatedById":223169,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-02T20:09:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI *Really* want this. I like the idea of having to discover planets first...even having them show as blurry in the tracking station until you reach the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E. That would create such a huge sense of excitement for discovering new planets, even ones modded in...the excitement of the approach...the immediate noticing that something is funky (seeing a blurry rask/rusk or a blurry ringed planet)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HammerTyme","CreatedById":227259,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-04T00:14:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAwesome idea!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Thundy","CreatedById":208895,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-04T13:58:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think it would be awesome to add telescope instrument parts (sensors, Mirrors, Lenses) instead of complete fully working telescopes (\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/SENTINEL_Infrared_Telescope\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ESENTINEL Infrared Telescope\u003C/a\u003E ) because that would allow for greater customizability and ability to fold them in interesting ways to future proof it for the Robotics parts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheArturro","CreatedById":225694,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-04T14:15:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224249855\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022213958\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221677768910\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022226666\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Tazooka\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3/2/2023 at 3:55 PM, Tazooka said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, that\u0027d be amazing and fun\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003EAlso you have a type in your signature\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFebruary\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you! I didn\u0027t notice it before \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kennyc222","CreatedById":209626,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-04T23:54:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt will be fun! but I have to wait when some critical bugs are fixed!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vl3d","CreatedById":219348,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-07T16:11:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis was already confirmed a long time ago.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tazooka","CreatedById":226666,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-07T19:06:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224254036\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022213958\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221678205490\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022219348\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vl3d\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Vl3d said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis was already confirmed a long time ago.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt was? Where? Do you have a link to the source, as I\u0027d love to see it \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vl3d","CreatedById":219348,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-07T19:28:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 d